reviewBlob: "Bud Heavy" is great for a good game of beer-pong, but I wouldnt want to sit down and drink it with dinner.
"Drinkability" is what the new slogan states. I say that it has no taste whatsoever. No aroma, Piss yellow color, its just terrible. Its not as bad as Miller Lite, but its down there.

beerName: Carolina Beer Co. Cottonwood Pumpkin Spiced Ale
reviewBlob: I had this beer last fall with a buddy and it was good. It had a nice pumpkin taste and aroma. I am a huge fan of pumpkin pie and this honestly tasted like one.
I despise this beer. No flavor, watery, very weak color, unless youre playing a lot of beer pong and you dont care about anything but getting drunk, dont go near this one!
Without a lime, its not a good beer. The color is weak and the taste is lacking and is almost bitter. Like I sad, unless youre throwing a Cinco de Mayo party, I wouldnt go near it.
This is my favorite Mexican restaurant beer. It is great to drink with ACP. It has a deep Amber color to it and is very rich and hearty. I must say that I enjoy this beer a lot.

brewerName: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
reviewBlob: The lemony smell and taste make this a decent choice for a Summer-time beer. The citrus taste overpowers the hops, but it wasnt terrible.
Its a cheap frat beer. Probably my favorite light beer, but lacks in color, taste, and smell. I only drink it if its the only thing in the fridge.

Its a nice dark amber color with a strong flavor. I am not much on heavy beers, but I can appreciate the beer for what it is. Its definitely a one time drinker, dont want to go throwing a bunch of these back.

beerName: Blue Moon Honey Moon Summer Ale
reviewBlob: Honey and orange citrus taste. Its a decent summer-time beer. I liked it, but the sweetness was a little much, I would only drink one...its not a 6 pack pounder.
Nice wheat ale. Goes good with an orange slice. Its a little sweet, but I kind of like that sometimes. The color is weak, but thats to be expected in a wheat ale.

Being from the Greensboro area, I absolutely love this beer. It is a great beer to drink with a steak dinner. It has a nutty & caramel taste and looks great coming out of the tap. The only problem I have is that the Brewery doesnt bottle it yet, so I have to go to a local bar and pay $3.00 to get it.
This beer is a good one. Its the oldest brewed beer in America and it has a great aroma and I love the way it pours. The deep amber color and the rich taste
